+# 0231 — Scheduler EventBus supervisor source
+
+## Purpose
+
+This patch makes the Scheduler visible to the passive supervision path as an
+upstream EventBus source without making the supervisor a scheduler adapter.
+
+Canonical path:
+
+```text
+Scheduler = upstream orchestration authority
+Scheduler event -> EventBus -> PassiveSupervisorSink = downstream-only observer
+PassiveSupervisorSink -> CellularState / optional snapshot / optional audit
+```
+
+## What is implemented
+
+`0231` extends the existing passive supervisor module introduced by `0220` and
+extended by `0230`:
+
+- `scheduler_supervision_event(...)` builds a canonical `BusSupervisorEvent`
+  with `cell_kind="SCHEDULER"`.
+- `PassiveSupervisorSink.accept_scheduler_event(...)` accepts a scheduler-originated
+  event through the existing sink.
+- `tools/run_scheduler_eventbus_supervisor_smoke_0231.py` demonstrates the
+  downstream-only path using a Scheduler-shaped EventBus event.
+
+## Authority boundary
+
+Scheduler remains the authority for orchestration. The passive supervisor only
+observes Scheduler events after they are emitted/exposed to the EventBus.
+
+Forbidden:
+
+```text
+Scheduler.run() is forbidden
+Scheduler handler dispatch is forbidden
+Scheduler mutation is forbidden
+new EventBus creation is forbidden
+proxy control is forbidden
+SHM mutation is forbidden
+policy decision is forbidden
+SQL/Qdrant/GitHub mutation is forbidden
+```
+
+## Reuse decision
+
+This patch reuses:
+
+```text
+BusSupervisorEvent
+PassiveSupervisorSink
+build_cellular_snapshot
+snapshot/audit optional outputs
+```
+
+It does not create a new runtime, a new bus, or a parallel scheduler surface.
